    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "In this hadith from al-Amali of Shaykh al-Saduq, transmitted through the Golden Chain (silsilat al-dhahab) through all twelve Imams, Imam Ali (AS) delivers a pithy reminder about the transience of worldly life. He warns that many people who are absorbed in material pursuits — weaving clothes and building homes — are unknowingly preparing for their own death, as those garments may become their burial shrouds and those homes the sites of their graves. This saying encapsulates a core Shi'i ethical theme about remembrance of death (dhikr al-mawt) as a corrective to heedlessness (ghafla).",
